Program: The History Hour
Title: Vera Brittain: Anti-Bombing Campaigner
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3cswqlw
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 19 Aug 2018
Baroness Shirley Williams recalls her mother, WW2 anti-bombing protestor; 20 years since a mass killing in Omagh, the African-American photographer whose coverage of Martin Luther King's funeral won him a Pullitzer Prize, plus when TV finally came to South Africa and the birth of the instant noodle. Photo: Vera Brittain at Euston Station, London, in 1956. Credit: Central Press/Hulton Archive/Getty Images Show less